---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Obsidian — Julien Klein">
  <div style="max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem;">
    <div style="padding: 3rem 0 1rem;">
      <a href="/ressources" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: #8B7355;">← Ressources</a>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><span style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8rem; color: #7A5C8B; border: 1px solid #7A5C8B; padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 999px;">Outil</span> <span style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8rem; color: #8B7355; border: 1px solid #D4C9B5; padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 999px;">Second Brain</span></div>
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem; color: #2C2416;">Obsidian</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #8B7355; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">Le cœur du Second Brain. Notes, Digital Garden, projets, captures — tout passe par Obsidian. Les fichiers sont en Markdown local, donc Claude peut les lire directement. Aucune dépendance cloud propriétaire.</p>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
      <div style="padding: 1.2rem; background: #FAF7F2; border: 1px solid #D4C9B5; border-radius: 10px;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #8B7355; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Pourquoi Obsidian</div>
        <div style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #2C2416; line-height: 1.6;">Fichiers locaux en Markdown = portables, lisibles par Claude, sauvegardables dans git. Pas de lock-in.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="padding: 1.2rem; background: #FAF7F2; border: 1px solid #D4C9B5; border-radius: 10px;">
        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: #8B7355; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Usage quotidien</div>
        <div style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #2C2416; line-height: 1.6;">Capture rapide via Wispr Flow, organisation automatique via <code>/capture</code>, lecture et écriture via Claude Code.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-size: 1rem; font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #2C2416;">Comment je l'utilise</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0;">
      {[
        "Vault principal : tout le Second Brain en Markdown local",
        "Structure PARA adaptée : Projects, Areas, Resources, Archive",
        "Daily Notes pour les captures rapides du jour",
        "Digital Garden : les notes matures liées à ce site",
        "Templates pour les types de notes récurrentes",
        "Sync via iCloud sur iPhone pour capturer en déplacement"
      ].map((step, i) => (
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: baseline; padding: 0.7rem 0; border-top: 1px solid #D4C9B5;">
          <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #8B7355; font-family: monospace; flex-shrink: 0;">{String(i+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span>
          <span style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: #2C2416;">{step}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 3rem; padding-bottom: 5rem;">
      <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: #8B7355; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Skills qui s'y connectent</div>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/ressources/skills/capture" style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem; border: 1px solid #D4C9B5; border-radius: 6px; color: #2C2416;">/capture →</a>
        <a href="/ressources/skills/ingest" style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem; border: 1px solid #D4C9B5; border-radius: 6px; color: #2C2416;">/ingest →</a>
        <a href="/ressources/skills/angle" style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem; border: 1px solid #D4C9B5; border-radius: 6px; color: #2C2416;">/angle →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
